Class App

java.lang.Object
com.Software.FitnessSystem.App
public class App extends Object
Main application class to manage the fitness system, including loading data, handling login, and saving data.
Author:
Muath Hassoun, Alaa Alawneh, Ammar Shafii

  • Constructor Details

    • App

      public App()
      Constructs an instance of the Fitness Management System. Initializes all system data by loading it from persistent storage. Also sets up user subscription plans and program enrollment statistics.

  • Method Details

    • main

    • printWelcomeMessage

      public static void printWelcomeMessage()
      Prints a welcome message to the console.

    • login

      public static String login(String userName, String role)
      Logs in a user based on their username, password, and role. Updates login statistics and session data for the user.
      Parameters:
      userName - The username of the user.
      role - The role of the user ("Admin", "Instructor", or "Client").
      Returns:
      A string indicating the result of the login attempt: "AdminLoggedIn", "InstructorLoggedIn", "ClientLoggedIn", "InvalidLogIn", or "NoOneLoggedIn".

    • instructorLogIn

      public static String instructorLogIn(String formattedDateTime)
      Handles the login process for an instructor. Updates the instructor's last login time and increments the login count. Saves updated instructor data back to persistent storage.
      Parameters:
      formattedDateTime - The current date and time formatted as a string.
      Returns:
      A string indicating a successful instructor login: "InstructorLoggedIn".

    • clientLogIn

      public static String clientLogIn(String formattedDateTime)
      Handles the login process for a client. Updates the client's last login time and increments the login count. Saves updated client data back to persistent storage.
      Parameters:
      formattedDateTime - The current date and time formatted as a string.
      Returns:
      A string indicating a successful client login: "ClientLoggedIn".
